I need to get back to this. I think perhaps the interface for defining commands could be improved. Instead of a single regex, it could have the command and parameters specified as function parameters, which were added to python in version 3 (which mpsyt requires, so that is not an issue). Something like this:

    @commands.command
    def thecommand(command: r"(thecommand)\s+", param1: r"(\S+)\s*$"):

Perhaps spaces should be handled by the software.

