@ahmadalattar242,  I think that is multiple output covered in ddpg. 

However, I personally do not recommend you to use DQN for multiple outputs. You need to define single output for multiple outputs. Suppose you have two possible actions for grip and two for orientation, you would need to define four actions which cover all the possible situation arising from the two action outputs. Please proceed ahead with DDPG. 

